  "prompt": "From where to get 350kv DC electronic transformer?",
  "response": "To obtain a 350kV DC electronic transformer, you would typically need to approach specialized manufacturers or suppliers that deal with high-voltage power equipment. Here are some avenues you can explore:\n\n1. **Specialized High-Voltage Equipment Manufacturers**:\n   - Companies that specialize in high-voltage components, such as transformers, power supplies, and related equipment, are the best starting points.\n   - Examples include Spellman High Voltage, Siemens Energy, GE Grid Solutions, and ABB.\n\n2. **Custom Engineering Solutions**:\n   - If you need a highly specific transformer, you may need to work with a company that offers custom engineering services. These companies can design and manufacture transformers to meet your exact specifications.\n\n3. **Industrial Suppliers and Distributors**:\n   - Some industrial suppliers or distributors may carry or have access to high-voltage transformers. Examples include Grainger, Mouser Electronics, or Digi-Key, though they may not stock such high-specification items directly.\n\n4. **Research and Development Institutions**:\n   - Universities or research labs that work with high-voltage technology might have connections to suppliers or even develop their own custom equipment.\n\n5. **Online Marketplaces and B2B Platforms**:\n   - Websites like Alibaba, ThomasNet, or Made-in-China often list manufacturers and suppliers of high-voltage equipment. You can search for specific products, request quotes, and compare offerings.\n\n6. **Energy and Utility Sector Suppliers**:\n   - Companies that supply equipment to the energy and utility sectors often deal with high-voltage transformers for applications like power transmission and distribution.\n\n7. **Networking and Industry Events**:\n   - Attend trade shows, conferences, or industry events related to power electronics, electrical engineering, or high-voltage technology. These are excellent opportunities to connect with suppliers and manufacturers.\n\n### Key Considerations:\n- **Custom Requirements**: Ensure you clearly specify your requirements, including voltage, current, size, weight, cooling method, and any other relevant parameters.\n- **Compliance and Certification**: Verify that the transformer meets relevant safety and industry standards (e.g., IEC, IEEE, UL).\n- **Cost and Lead Time**: High-voltage transformers can be expensive and may have long lead times, especially for custom designs.\n- **Technical Support**: Ensure the supplier offers technical support for installation, operation, and maintenance.\n\nIf you provide more details about your specific application or requirements, I can help refine the search further.",
